does it break a dvd player sitting a vcr on top of it it depends if the vcr is heavier than the dvd player it might break it in that case the other way around would work out bottom line watch out if your dvd player has air vents on the top and make sure the vcr is lighter than the dvd player otherwise a vcr on the dvd player could break the dvd player hope this is helpful advise Macrovision Laserdisc Live Aid Copy protection VHS Videocassette recorder Survivor (TV series) DVD DVD recorder DVD player Video CD SCART Compact disc Snooker Diving suit Betamax IPod Napoleon Dynamite Billiards Star Trek: Enterprise S__CAM Poker jargon S-VHS PAL Sega Mega Drive/Sega Genesis Integrated Services Digital Broadcasting Composite monitor Bong Hot air balloon Sony Corp. of America v. Universal City Studios, Inc. Camcorder Cable television Volleyball Dance Dance Revolution EXTREME Embouchure Videotape Cello DDRMAX: Dance Dance Revolution Big Brother (USA TV series) Nottingham Forest F.C. Oasis (band) DDRMAX: Dance Dance Revolution 6thMIX Tris Speaker DDRMAX2: Dance Dance Revolution 7thMIX M16 (rifle) High-definition television Press Your Luck DDRMAX2: Dance Dance Revolution Capacitor plague Xbox The Footy Show High fidelity Airsoft Ayumi Hamasaki Lewis Galoob Toys, Inc. v. Nintendo of America, Inc. History of Test cricket (to 1883) Digital video recorder DualDisc World Poker Tour Collective Soul Star Wars Episode V: The Empire Strikes Back Reggie Jackson Panzer I Anchor SelectaVision Queen (band) Shogun: Total War TiVo Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope YUV Andre Agassi Dance Dance Revolution EXTREME (North America) Floorball Comparison of media players Harmonica Paintball West Bromwich Albion F.C. Lost film Casting Toronto Blue Jays Home cinema Draw poker The Mary Tyler Moore Show Texas hold 'em The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King (film) Opeth Vehicles in Unreal Tournament 2004 DeCSS Hi-hat EverQuest Thermal power station Nintendo Revolution Cheating in poker Dubbing (film